<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-30T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/47<hi rend="superscript">7/22</hi>: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Southard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-30T17:00:00+08:00">June
                                        30, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 30—7:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>220. Reference Department’s 103, June 28, 7 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">6
                                    p.m.</hi>]. Governor of Hong Kong has today telegraphed through
                                British Consul General at Saigon to Governor General of Indochina
                                his approval of shipment of stocks of wolfram and antimony to the
                                United States.</p>
                            <p>I am telegraphing Reed at Hanoi to get in touch with Bell of the
                                Pekin Syndicate who is handling shipping arrangements at Haiphong as
                                the Governor here has requested me to do so.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Department.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>